1) Design Thinking and clearly defining developer pain points are obvious starting points for Developer Journeys

2) Use Cases define the tasks that the developers perform on their Journey. They can be industry-specific or not, but it is best if they 
    are not
    
3) Use cases are based on underlying Architecture Patterns, which often are cross-industry.

4) Code snippets rather than Sample Apps.  In today's cloud space sample apps have a very short half-life  because they have too many moving parts and  
    dependencies and are seldom maintained.  
   
